01 June - Cream Puff Shells

- 1   cup water
- 1/2 cup butter
- 1/4 teaspoon salt
- 1   cup flour
- 4   eggs

Put water, butter, salt in a sauce pan. Heat to boiling. Add teh flour all at once and stir vigorously until mixture no long clings to the pan. Remove from heat and cool slightly. Add eggs one at a atime, beating vigrorously each time the egg is added. Take up tablespoons fo mix and put on a well buttered baking sheet. Leave 2 inches between puffs. Bake in a hot 450F oven for 20 minutes, reduce heat to 325 and bake for about 20 minutes longer. Watch the cooking process. 